    "An interesting case is the suicide map: GPT only used risk factors (although the document contains an abundance of protective factors), hence every causation should have been increasing.",
    "However, 45% of edges were mislabeled as a decrease.",
    "Common issues were a lack of understanding of the temporal sequence of events.",
    "For example, GPT views that stress will increase prior suicide attempts, and controversial Table 3: We use 12 filters, divided into low-level Python filters (1-9 and 12) and high-level filters (10, 11) that send additional prompts to GPT.",
    "Our guiding example illustrates that GPT returns part of the prompt (here 'keyphrase') when it fails to answer."
